@startuml sandbox
!include ../_includes/style.iuml

title Sandbox — slice 2d code-tests isolation (Dαα, opt-in, fail-closed)

package "src/main/modelhub/routing/sandbox/" {
  component "index.ts\n• getSandbox({enabled})\n• dispatch by\n  process.platform" as IDX
  component "types.ts\n• SandboxProvider (ABC)\n• SandboxResult\n• SandboxOptions\n• SandboxUnavailable" as TYPES

  component "unsafe.ts\n• UnsafeSandbox\n• throws every time\n• default when opt-in off" as UNSAFE
  component "posix.ts\n• PosixSandbox\n• rlimits NPROC=cur,\n  AS/DATA=512 MiB,\n  CPU=10s, FSIZE=0\n• detached pgrp\n• kill -pgid on timeout\n• `python -I -S -B`" as POSIX
  component "windows.ts\n• WindowsSandbox\n• dispatches to PS1" as WIN
  component "win-job.ps1\n• Add-Type P/Invoke\n• CreateJobObject\n• ActiveProcessLimit=1\n• ProcessMemoryLimit\n  =512 MiB\n• KILL_ON_JOB_CLOSE\n• marker-line streams" as PS1
}

component "characterizeRunner.ts\n(builds runSandbox seam)" as RUNNER
component "staircase.evaluateItem()\n(catches throw ⇒ UNMEASURED)" as STAIR

RUNNER --> IDX : getSandbox({enabled})
IDX --> UNSAFE : enabled:false\n(default) OR\nunknown OS
IDX --> POSIX : enabled:true\n+ linux/darwin
IDX --> WIN : enabled:true\n+ win32

WIN --> PS1 : spawn powershell.exe\n-File win-job.ps1
POSIX ..> "python3\n(child)" : spawn\ndetached:true
PS1 ..> "python.exe\n(child)" : Process.Start +\nAssignProcessToJobObject

UNSAFE -.-> STAIR : throws\nSandboxUnavailable
POSIX -.-> STAIR : {pass:bool} OR\nthrows on\nUNMEASURED
WIN -.-> STAIR : {pass:bool} OR\nthrows on\nUNMEASURED

note bottom of IDX
  Fail-closed (Dαα §3):
  ANY impossibility to set the
  kernel boundary ⇒ throw
  SandboxUnavailable ⇒ caller
  marks the item UNMEASURED.
  **Never** a false pass.
end note

note right of POSIX
  Defense-in-depth preamble blocks
  imports (socket, subprocess,
  ctypes, …) — trivially bypassable,
  the rlimits ARE the boundary.
end note

@enduml
